"common bile duct-ampulla of vater, external approach. this class includes one or more of 24 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the common bile duct and the ampulla of vater with external approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0f.. . "
"common bile duct-ampulla of vater, external approach. this class includes one or more of 24 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the common bile duct and the ampulla of vater with external approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0f.. fragmentation in ampulla of vater,  external approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to fragmentation in ampulla of vater,  external approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0ffcxzz. "

"liver hepatic duct-hepatobiliary duct, natural or artificial opening-part a. this class includes one or more of 24 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the liver and hepatic duct and hepatobiliary duct  via natural or artificial opening.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0f.. dilation of right hepatic duct with intraluminal device,  via natural or artificial opening endoscopic. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to dilation of right hepatic duct with intraluminal device,  via natural or artificial opening endoscopic.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0f758dz. "

"

"
